      "text": "Blob\nstore\n(S3)",
      "fontSize": 18.76234628827427,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "bEGPwmdHB2Q-gDG8Qxwra",
      "originalText": "Blob store\n(S3)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "24XixFwejHpnFroWt-YMn",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1500.4036798158304,
      "y": 2059.6409320885086,
      "width": 638.2396240234375,
      "height": 250,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aa",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2002796835,
      "version": 831,
      "versionNonce": 1294019085,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776440621812,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Naive way is to send entire doc to the websocket endpoint\nand evey key press / text sends a request and stores it to\nthe blob storage\nIssues : \n1) We can have few bytes of data or megabytes of data \nfor multi-page doc, it's not feasible to send that kind of payload\nfrequently.\n2) Writing entire documents to blob storage have consistency \nissues, last user updates the doc which is stored in the db\nwhen users are modifying simultaneously (non-collaborative).",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Naive way is to send entire doc to the websocket endpoint\nand evey key press / text sends a request and stores it to\nthe blob storage\nIssues : \n1) We can have few bytes of data or megabytes of data \nfor multi-page doc, it's not feasible to send that kind of payload\nfrequently.\n2) Writing entire documents to blob storage have consistency \nissues, last user updates the doc which is stored in the db\nwhen users are modifying simultaneously (non-collaborative).",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "It1M8nWEGi06lBNxYK97P",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1494.19150345058,
      "y": 1738.12362197235,
      "width": 621.6841430664062,
      "height": 268.7141418457031,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "ab",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1979008365,
      "version": 812,
      "versionNonce": 820666477,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776440621812,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Collaborative editing algorithms\n--------------------------------------\n1) CRDT (Conflict-free replicated data types)\nGreat for offline applications, offset based allocation of letters.\nMemory intensive. Better for P2P setting.\n\n2) OT (Operational Transform)\nRelies on a central server, transform operations\nof different users, guarantees consistent view\nfor all users after operations are applied.\nHigher performance",
      "fontSize": 19.5428466796875,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Collaborative editing algorithms\n--------------------------------------\n1) CRDT (Conflict-free replicated data types)\nGreat for offline applications, offset based allocation of letters.\nMemory intensive. Better for P2P setting.\n\n2) OT (Operational Transform)\nRelies on a central server, transform operations\nof different users, guarantees consistent view\nfor all users after operations are applied.\nHigher performance",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
