      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776368135890,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Transform Ops\nbefore persisting to db",
      "fontSize": 18.76234628827427,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Transform Ops\nbefore persisting to db",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "hlHwhq5G4JylYV5Er914j",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2243.9165281668174,
      "y": 1807.9016894378258,
      "width": 637.2195434570312,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "ap",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 171964003,
      "version": 1184,
      "versionNonce": 336336941,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776441891533,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1) When an offline user comes to the doc link and new ws\nconn is created in the Document service, the event\ntriggers read of all ops from db and then send an update\nmsg via ws and send them to the new user, now they\nare caught up.\n\n2) Non-trivial case when users are live and editing simultaneously,\nthe Document Service does the transformations from multiple\nusers, store it in DB and then send the updates to all of them\n. If only one user is authoring and others viewing then we send\nthe changes to all users except the author.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1) When an offline user comes to the doc link and new ws\nconn is created in the Document service, the event\ntriggers read of all ops from db and then send an update\nmsg via ws and send them to the new user, now they\nare caught up.\n\n2) Non-trivial case when users are live and editing simultaneously,\nthe Document Service does the transformations from multiple\nusers, store it in DB and then send the updates to all of them\n. If only one user is authoring and others viewing then we send\nthe changes to all users except the author.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
